#Correcting Nutral Value field data from 0/1 to Yes/No
#Correcting and merging same stadiam names
import re
class clsCleanData():
    def __init__(self,datacol):
        self.strcoldata=datacol
    def funcCleanNutralvenue(self):
        lstNutralVenue=[]
        for strNutralVenue in self.strcoldata:
            if(strNutralVenue=="0"):
                strNutralVenueFinal=re.sub("0","No",strNutralVenue)
            else:
                strNutralVenueFinal=re.sub("1","Yes",strNutralVenue)
            lstNutralVenue.append(strNutralVenueFinal)
        return lstNutralVenue
    def FuncVenueClean(self):
        lstVenueFinal=[]
        for strvenue in self.strcoldata:
            if(strvenue=='M.Chinnaswamy Stadium,Bengaluru'):
                lstVenueFinal.append(re.sub("M.Chinnaswamy Stadium,Bengaluru","M Chinnaswamy Stadium,Bangalore",strvenue))
            elif(strvenue=='Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali,Chandigarh'):
                lstVenueFinal.append(re.sub("Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali,Chandigarh",
                                            "Punjab Cricket Association Stadium, Mohali,Chandigarh",strvenue))
            else:
                lstVenueFinal.append(strvenue)
        return lstVenueFinal

#function to calculate win %
class clsCalculatePerc():
    def __init__(self,TotalMatch,MatchWin):
        self.lstTotalMatch=TotalMatch
        self.lstMatchWin=MatchWin
    def FuncWinPercent(self):
        lstWinPercTemp=[]
        for i in range(0,len(self.lstTotalMatch)):
            DblPercent=((self.lstMatchWin[i]/self.lstTotalMatch[i])*100)
            #lstWinPercTemp.append("%.2f" % DblPercent)
            lstWinPercTemp.append(int(DblPercent))
        return lstWinPercTemp

# function to add value labels
def funcshowvalue(x,y,barnum):
    for i in range(len(x)):
        if(barnum==1):
            plt.text(i, y[i], y[i], ha = 'center')
        elif(barnum==2):
            plt.text(i+0.35,y[i],y[i],ha='center')

#Data prepare for chart 3,4,5 - Batting first & Fielding first data analysis
class clsBatFieldCalc():
    def __init__(self,toss_decs,toss_win,team1,team2):
        self.strTossDecision=toss_decs
        self.strTossWinner=toss_win
        self.strTeam1=team1
        self.strTeam2=team2
    def FuncBatFieldCol(self):
        lstBatFirstTemp=[]
        lstFieldFirstTemp=[]
        for i in range(0,len(self.strTossDecision)):
            if(self.strTossDecision[i]=="bat"):
                lstBatFirstTemp.append(self.strTossWinner[i])
                if(self.strTossWinner[i]==self.strTeam1[i]):
                    lstFieldFirstTemp.append(self.strTeam2[i])
                else:
                    lstFieldFirstTemp.append(self.strTeam1[i])
            else:
                lstFieldFirstTemp.append(self.strTossWinner[i])
                if(self.strTossWinner[i]==self.strTeam1[i]):
                    lstBatFirstTemp.append(self.strTeam2[i])
                else:
                    lstBatFirstTemp.append(self.strTeam1[i])
        return lstBatFirstTemp,lstFieldFirstTemp

#function to calculate count of win batting first & fielding first
class clsMatchWinCnt():
    def FuncBatFirstWinCnt(self,strTeam,strBattingTeam,strWinner):
        lstBattingWinCntTemp=[]
        for i in strTeam:
            IntBattingWinCnt=0
            for j in range(0,len(strBattingTeam)):
                if(i==strBattingTeam[j] and i==strWinner[j]):
                    IntBattingWinCnt=IntBattingWinCnt+1
            lstBattingWinCntTemp.append(IntBattingWinCnt)
        return lstBattingWinCntTemp
    def FuncFieldFirstWinCnt(self,strTeam,strFieldTeam,strWinner):
        lstFieldWinCntTemp=[]
        for i in strTeam:
            IntFieldWinCnt=0
            for j in range(0,len(strFieldTeam)):
                if(i==strFieldTeam[j] and i==strWinner[j]):
                    IntFieldWinCnt=IntFieldWinCnt+1
            lstFieldWinCntTemp.append(IntFieldWinCnt)
        return lstFieldWinCntTemp

# function to calculate home & away win 
class clsHomeAwayWinCnt():
    def __init__(self,hometeam,awayteam,team1,team2,nutral,winner):
        self.strHomeTeam=hometeam
        self.strAwayTeam=awayteam
        self.strTeam1=team1
        self.strTeam2=team2
        self.strNutral=nutral
        self.strWinner=winner
    def FuncHomeWinCnt(self):
        lstHomeWinTemp=[]
        for i in self.strHomeTeam:
            IntHomeWinCnt=0
            for j in range(0,len(self.strTeam1)):
                if((i==self.strTeam1[j]) and (i==self.strWinner[j]) and self.strNutral[j]=="No"):
                    #print(self.strTeam1)
                    IntHomeWinCnt=IntHomeWinCnt+1
            #print(i)
            #print(IntHomeWinCnt)
            lstHomeWinTemp.append(IntHomeWinCnt)
        return(lstHomeWinTemp)
    def FuncAwayWinCnt(self):
        lstAwayWinTemp=[]
        for i in self.strAwayTeam:
            IntAwayWinCnt=0
            for j in range(len(self.strTeam2)):
                if((i==self.strTeam2[j]) and (i==self.strWinner[j]) and self.strNutral[j]=="No"):
                    #print(self.strTeam1)
                    IntAwayWinCnt=IntAwayWinCnt+1
            #print(i)
            #print(IntHomeWinCnt)
            lstAwayWinTemp.append(IntAwayWinCnt)
        return(lstAwayWinTemp)

# function to calculate win count batting first & second in each ground
class clsVenueWinCnt():
    def __init__(self,stedium,bat,field,winner,venuecity):
        self.strstedium=stedium
        self.strBattingTeam=bat
        self.strFieldingTeam=field
        self.strWinner=winner
        self.strVenue=venuecity
    def funcVenueWinCnt(self):
        lstFirstBatWinTemp=[]
        lstFirstFieldWinTemp=[]
        for i in self.strstedium:
            IntFirstBatWin=0
            IntFirstFieldWin=0
            for j in range(0,len(self.strVenue)):
                if(i==self.strVenue[j]):
                    if(self.strBattingTeam[j]==self.strWinner[j]):
                        IntFirstBatWin=IntFirstBatWin+1
                    elif(self.strFieldingTeam[j]==self.strWinner[j]):
                        IntFirstFieldWin=IntFirstFieldWin+1
            lstFirstBatWinTemp.append(IntFirstBatWin)
            lstFirstFieldWinTemp.append(IntFirstFieldWin)
        return lstFirstBatWinTemp,lstFirstFieldWinTemp
